    <note>Zhang(1) Ju(2) [209] One of four close friends: himself, Jiang(3) Zhiji [461], Hu(1) Zongyu [833] and Ding(1) Zhi [3849]. He followed Hu Yuan [3404] when young and studied the Yijing with Ouyang(1) Xiu [1384]. It is possible that this is not the same Zhang Ju who was appointed to fiscal office in 1099. However, the other connections are still valid. According to Yang(2) Shi's [2022] funerary inscription for Ju's younger brother, Xu(4) [13680] (1065-1122) (q.v.), Ju did not achieve a high position, but because of the associations cited above, this Jinling Zhang became a distinguished lineage (zhuxing) from this time forward. XCB, 512.11a; Piling zhi, 17.12a. CBD, 3, 2226.</note>
